page: 1" ', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' *************************************************************************** ', u'\n', u' MARKER PAGE="sheet: 1; page: 1" ', u'\n', u' ', u'Appendix\n    A', u' ', u'\n', u' ', u'\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0Below\n    is certain information regarding the non-GAAP financial information that\n    appears in the attached Lenders\x92 Presentation dated August 10, 2004\n    (as revised on August 24, 2004). ', u' ', u'\n', u' ', u'\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0Adjusted\n    EBITDA is presented in the Lenders\x92 Presentation because Mueller Group,\n    Inc.\x92s (the \x93Company\x94) Second Amended and Restated Credit\n    Agreement, dated as of April 23, 2004 (the \x93Senior Credit Facility\x94),\n    contains certain covenants that utilize this measure of Adjusted EBITDA.\n    Adjusted EBITDA is defined in the Senior Credit Facility (see Exhibit 10.03\n    to the Mueller Holdings (N.A.), Inc. Form S-4 (file no. 333-116590)). The\n    Senior Credit Facility is considered material to the Company because borrowings\n    under it comprise a significant portion of the Company\x92s debt.', u' ', u'\n', u' ', u'\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0The\n    following non-GAAP financial measures, which are also included in the Lenders\x92 Presentation,\n    are considered useful measures by lenders in evaluating the proposed amendments\n    to the Senior Credit Facility: ', u' ', u'\n', u'\n', u'free cash flow = adjusted\n      EBITDA plus or minus changes in working capital, minus capital expenditures,\n      cash interest and cash taxes', u'\n', u'\n', u'net leverage = (total\n      debt minus cash) / adjusted EBITDA', u'\n', u'\n', u'interest coverage =\n      adjusted EBITDA / pro forma interest expense', u'\n', u'\n', u'pro forma interest\n      expense = GAAP interest expense as adjusted for deferred financing fees,\n      early debt extinguishment fees and certain mark-to-market adjustments', u'\n', u'\n', u'pro forma as adjusted\n      interest expense = pro forma interest expense as adjusted for the proposed\n      amendment to the Senior Credit Facility', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' ', u'Adjusted EBITDA and the\n    other measures described above:', u' ', u'\n', u'\n', u'have not been prepared\n      in accordance with U.S. GAAP;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'may not be comparable\n      to similarly titled measures reported by other companies;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'should not be considered\n      an alternative to, or more meaningful than, GAAP information;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'have limitations as\n      analytical tools;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'should not be considered\n      in isolation;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'do not reflect the\n      Company\x92s cash expenditures, or future requirements, for capital expenditures\n      or contractual commitments;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' *************************************************************************** ', u'\n', u' MARKER PAGE="sheet: 1; page: 1" ', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u' ', u'\n', u'\n', u'do not reflect changes\n      in, or cash requirements for, our working capital needs;', u'\n', u'\n', u'\n', u'do not reflect the\n      significant interest expense, or the cash requirements necessary to service\n      interest or
